{"article_id":"ht34z5pD40oMs4ad","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Violence Erupts","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"As Outrage Over George Floyd 's Death Spills Into A New Week","depth":2},{"id":2,"text":"Protesters staged large-scale demonstrations across the country on Sunday ,","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"expressing outrage at the death of George Floyd in Minneapolis and , more broadly , anger at police brutality .","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"Some cities ,","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"including Minneapolis , Atlanta and Louisville ,","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"saw clashes with police , buildings and cars set afire , and looting .","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"By evening , many demonstrations had given way to another night of violence and destruction ,","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"with protesters ignoring curfews","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"imposed in dozens of cities .","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"Police used tear gas and stun grenades and fired rubber bullets in attempts to disperse the crowds .","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"More than 17,000 National Guard troops have been activated in states across the U.S. due to civil unrest as of Monday ,","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"and that number is expected to grow .","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"Floyd , a 46-year-old black man , died in police custody last Monday .","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"Video shows","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"that a Minneapolis police officer had his knee on Floyd 's neck for nearly nine minutes shortly before his death .","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"Tensions were already simmering","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"following the deaths of Ahmaud Arbery in February and Breonna Taylor in March .","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"Arbery , a 25-year-old black man , was jogging through a Glynn County , Ga. , neighborhood","depth":11},{"id":19,"text":"when he was shot dead .","depth":11},{"id":20,"text":"Three white men were arrested last month","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"after state investigators took over the case from local authorities .","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"Protests also continued for a fourth straight night in Louisville , Ky. ,","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"as activists called for justice for Taylor .","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"Police shot and killed the 26-year-old black woman in her home .","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"In Minneapolis , a semitrailer plowed through a crowd of protesters","depth":12},{"id":26,"text":"marching on an interstate highway near downtown","depth":13},{"id":27,"text":"that had been closed to traffic .","depth":13},{"id":28,"text":"Authorities say","depth":13},{"id":29,"text":"no one was injured","depth":13},{"id":30,"text":"when the truck drove into the crowd at a high speed , westbound on Interstate 35 .","depth":12},{"id":31,"text":"According to the Minnesota Department of Public Safety ,","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"the driver may have been unaware of the highway closure .","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"`` It appears the semi was on I-35W","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"as authorities were closing the road .","depth":12},{"id":35,"text":"It did n't appear to drive through any barricades , ''","depth":11},{"id":36,"text":"the department tweeted .","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"Some protesters jumped on top of the truck ,","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"and","depth":12},{"id":39,"text":"as it stopped ,","depth":13},{"id":40,"text":"they dragged the driver out of the front seat","depth":14},{"id":41,"text":"and started beating him .","depth":14},{"id":42,"text":"The driver ,","depth":13},{"id":43,"text":"identified by police as Bogdan Vechirko of Otsego , Minn. ,","depth":13},{"id":44,"text":"is being held on probable cause for assault .","depth":12},{"id":45,"text":"He was taken to a hospital","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"and is being treated for his injuries .","depth":12},{"id":47,"text":"`` He was driving a gas tanker , ''","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"said Rhys Gailah , 39 ,","depth":12},{"id":49,"text":"who was in the middle of a sit-in","depth":14},{"id":50,"text":"listening to speakers","depth":14},{"id":51,"text":"when the truck came barreling through .","depth":13},{"id":52,"text":"`` He came driving at least 50 miles per hour through the crowd .","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"Everyone was sitting .","depth":12},{"id":54,"text":"It was peaceful . ''","depth":12},{"id":55,"text":"State Public Safety Commissioner John Harrington says","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"authorities had shut down the freeway","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"so that the protesters ,","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"who numbered from 4,000 to 5,000 ,","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"could safely demonstrate .","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"Before the incident , the protest had appeared peaceful .","depth":6},{"id":61,"text":"Washington , D.C. , authorities imposed a curfew after an evening of escalating demonstrations .","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"Protesters threw bottles at police","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"and set fires to cars and the basement of historic St. John 's Church ,","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"which has been visited by every president since James Madison .","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"`` Tonight 's curfew will begin at 7 p.m.","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"and will run for two days , ''","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"D.C. Mayor Muriel Bowser said at a late morning news conference on Monday .","depth":7},{"id":68,"text":"It 's primary day in the nation 's capital on Tuesday ,","depth":7},{"id":69,"text":"and the curfew goes into effect an hour before polls close at 8 p.m. ,","depth":7},{"id":70,"text":"according to the District of Columbia Board of Elections website .","depth":6},{"id":71,"text":"The protests on Sunday began","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"with peaceful marchers , along with a police escort , moving their way along a nearly 2-mile stretch from Howard University to Lafayette Square in front of the White House .","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"Protesters chanted about the death of Floyd and other African Americans","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"who have died","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"following police violence .","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"`` Even in the middle of a pandemic , cops are killing us , ''","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"read a sign","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"carried by protester Elizabeth Betts .","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"`` It 's crazy how","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"even in the middle of a pandemic , black people have to protest like this , ''","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"she said .","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"`` We are at a point","depth":12},{"id":83,"text":"where it 's the same story ,","depth":13},{"id":84,"text":"the same things are happening .","depth":13},{"id":85,"text":"I 'm tired of this . ''","depth":11},{"id":86,"text":"But","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"after clashes with law enforcement and the fires erupting ,","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"police pushed the crowds away from the White House with bursts of tear gas .","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"Kentucky 's governor said","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"that one person died early Monday","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"as security forces confronted a crowd in central Louisville .","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"`` While working to disperse a crowd ,","depth":12},{"id":93,"text":"[ Louisville Metro Police Department ] and the Kentucky National Guard were fired upon , ''","depth":12},{"id":94,"text":"Kentucky Gov . Andy Beshear said in a statement .","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"`` LMPD and the Kentucky National Guard returned fire","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"resulting in a death . ''","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"He announced","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"that the Kentucky State Police will be investigating the matter .","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"Louisville Mayor Greg Fischer tweeted his `` deepest condolences '' for the family of the man ,","depth":9},{"id":100,"text":"whom he identified as David McAtee .","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"Fischer also called for a Day of Reflection on Monday .","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"He held a late morning virtual gathering on Facebook with faith leaders after another night of demonstrations in the city over the death of Breonna Taylor .","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"On Sunday , law enforcement officers earlier fired tear gas into a crowd","depth":10},{"id":104,"text":"assembled in the Jefferson Square area of the city ,","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"NPR member station WFPL reported .","depth":9},{"id":106,"text":"At a Sunday evening news conference , Fischer again thanked those protesting peacefully","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"but said","depth":10},{"id":108,"text":"others were `` hijacking '' their efforts .","depth":10},{"id":109,"text":"Two Atlanta police officers have been terminated","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"and three others placed on desk duty","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"after a video of the arrest of two young African Americans","depth":12},{"id":112,"text":"leaving the protests Saturday night","depth":12},{"id":113,"text":"went viral .","depth":11},{"id":114,"text":"Atlanta Mayor Keisha Lance Bottoms announced the officers ' firing on Sunday ,","depth":12},{"id":115,"text":"saying","depth":13},{"id":116,"text":"the footage `` was disturbing on many levels . ''","depth":13},{"id":117,"text":"`` We understand","depth":13},{"id":118,"text":"our officers are working very long hours , under an enormous amount of stress , ''","depth":14},{"id":119,"text":"Bottoms said .","depth":14},{"id":120,"text":"`` But we also understand","depth":13},{"id":121,"text":"that the use of excessive force is never acceptable . ''","depth":13},{"id":122,"text":"Georgia Public Broadcasting reported","depth":12},{"id":123,"text":"that veteran officers Mark Gardner and Ivory Streeter were terminated .","depth":12},{"id":124,"text":"The footage from Streeter 's body camera shows the officers confronting the pair","depth":15},{"id":125,"text":"as the two were leaving the downtown protests","depth":16},{"id":126,"text":"after the 9 p.m. curfew went into effect .","depth":16},{"id":127,"text":"At roughly the 2:30 mark in the video , one of them is seen sitting in the driver 's seat of a car ,","depth":15},{"id":128,"text":"recording officers","depth":16},{"id":129,"text":"arresting someone else .","depth":16},{"id":130,"text":"An officer opens the car door","depth":15},{"id":131,"text":"and asks the driver","depth":16},{"id":132,"text":"if he wants to go to jail .","depth":16},{"id":133,"text":"Several minutes later , officers approach the car again .","depth":15},{"id":134,"text":"One uses a baton","depth":17},{"id":135,"text":"to smash the driver 's side window .","depth":17},{"id":136,"text":"Police then use a stun gun on the driver ,","depth":18},{"id":137,"text":"who has been identified by local media as Messiah Young .","depth":18},{"id":138,"text":"Georgia Public Broadcasting reported","depth":19},{"id":139,"text":"that Young suffered an epileptic seizure ,","depth":19},{"id":140,"text":"according to Spelman College 's Student Government Association .","depth":18},{"id":141,"text":"The second person , a woman","depth":16},{"id":142,"text":"who has since been identified as Taniyah Pilgrim ,","depth":16},{"id":143,"text":"has been released from custody","depth":15},{"id":144,"text":"and charges against her dropped .","depth":14},{"id":145,"text":"Footage","depth":16},{"id":146,"text":"posted by The Atlanta Journal-Constitution","depth":16},{"id":147,"text":"shows the passenger pleading with police to stop","depth":15},{"id":148,"text":"as they also use a stun gun against her .","depth":14},{"id":149,"text":"Vandalism and violence broke out after peaceful protests in Santa Monica and other parts of Southern California on Sunday - a sequence of events","depth":11},{"id":150,"text":"that has become familiar in many U.S. cities in the past week .","depth":11},{"id":151,"text":"The new round of destruction came","depth":11},{"id":152,"text":"despite a curfew and the presence of the National Guard .","depth":11},{"id":153,"text":"`` We tried kneeling , ''","depth":13},{"id":154,"text":"protester Jesus Guzman , 19 , told NPR 's Doualy Xaykaothao near the Santa Monica Pier .","depth":13},{"id":155,"text":"`` We tried putting on those T-shirts","depth":15},{"id":156,"text":"that said","depth":16},{"id":157,"text":"' I ca n't breathe . '","depth":16},{"id":158,"text":"We tried those hashtags .","depth":15},{"id":159,"text":"We tried doing it all peacefully ,","depth":15},{"id":160,"text":"but they have n't heard us -","depth":14},{"id":161,"text":"they have n't done nothing . ''","depth":14},{"id":162,"text":"With store windows smashed ,","depth":13},{"id":163,"text":"some shop owners in Santa Monica started cleaning up the mess overnight","depth":14},{"id":164,"text":"- the latest setback after weeks of forced closures","depth":15},{"id":165,"text":"because of the COVID-19 pandemic .","depth":15},{"id":166,"text":"At their hair salon , Martha Padilla-Bruni and her family were sweeping up broken glass under the streetlights .","depth":13},{"id":167,"text":"`` I 'm in shock .","depth":15},{"id":168,"text":"I do n't know","depth":16},{"id":169,"text":"what 's going to happen , ''","depth":16},{"id":170,"text":"Padilla-Bruni told NPR 's Nathan Rott .","depth":14},{"id":171,"text":"Her son , Joe Franco , said","depth":12},{"id":172,"text":"he supports the protesters and those","depth":13},{"id":173,"text":"who were there earlier in the day .","depth":13},{"id":174,"text":"He said","depth":13},{"id":175,"text":"he understands","depth":14},{"id":176,"text":"that people are in pain .","depth":14},{"id":177,"text":"Franco said ,","depth":13},{"id":178,"text":"`` But I was here across the street ,","depth":14},{"id":179,"text":"and what I saw ,","depth":15},{"id":180,"text":"the people","depth":18},{"id":181,"text":"that were doing this ...","depth":18},{"id":182,"text":"they were not here","depth":18},{"id":183,"text":"to protest .","depth":18},{"id":184,"text":"They were here","depth":17},{"id":185,"text":"to cause trouble . ''","depth":17},{"id":186,"text":"Reporter in Long Beach , Calif. , hit in throat by rubber bullet","depth":9},{"id":187,"text":"KPCC/LAist reporter Adolfo Guzman-Lopez was hit in the throat by a rubber bullet Sunday evening during protests in Long Beach , Calif .","depth":12},{"id":188,"text":"He believes","depth":13},{"id":189,"text":"the bullet was fired by Long Beach police ,","depth":14},{"id":190,"text":"who had been firing the projectiles nearby .","depth":14},{"id":191,"text":"`` I just got hit by a rubber bullet near the bottom of my throat , ''","depth":13},{"id":192,"text":"Guzman-Lopez said via Twitter ,","depth":14},{"id":193,"text":"posting an image of his wound .","depth":14},{"id":194,"text":"`` I had just interviewed a man with my phone at 3rd and Pine","depth":14},{"id":195,"text":"and a police officer aimed and shot me in the throat ,","depth":14},{"id":196,"text":"I saw the bullet bounce onto the street . ''","depth":13},{"id":197,"text":"Guzman-Lopez was able to breathe","depth":11},{"id":198,"text":"and was checked out by doctors Sunday night .","depth":11},{"id":199,"text":"The reporter said","depth":10},{"id":200,"text":"he had just finished interviewing a man","depth":12},{"id":201,"text":"who had been kneeling in protest","depth":12},{"id":202,"text":"when he himself was hit .","depth":11},{"id":203,"text":"`` I talked to him for about a minute ,","depth":11},{"id":204,"text":"and","depth":14},{"id":205,"text":"just as I was finishing talking to him","depth":17},{"id":206,"text":"-","depth":17},{"id":207,"text":"right after I said , 'Thank you ' -","depth":16},{"id":208,"text":"I heard a pop","depth":15},{"id":209,"text":"and I felt something ,","depth":16},{"id":210,"text":"you know ,","depth":17},{"id":211,"text":"the bottom of my throat ,","depth":17},{"id":212,"text":"and I saw something bounced onto the ground ,","depth":15},{"id":213,"text":"and then I ran , ''","depth":14},{"id":214,"text":"he said .","depth":12},{"id":215,"text":"`` As I was running ,","depth":12},{"id":216,"text":"I did start to feel its sting ,","depth":12},{"id":217,"text":"and then I put my fingers to my throat","depth":12},{"id":218,"text":"and there was blood on my fingers . ''","depth":12},{"id":219,"text":"A number of journalists have been hit with police projectiles during the protests ,","depth":3},{"id":220,"text":"including MSNBC 's Ali Velshi ,","depth":5},{"id":221,"text":"who was shot in the leg by a rubber bullet in Minneapolis ,","depth":5},{"id":222,"text":"and a Louisville TV reporter","depth":5},{"id":223,"text":"who was shot with pepper balls .","depth":5}],"relations":[{"parent":447,"left":225,"right":446,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":225,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":446,"left":441,"right":445,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":441,"left":283,"right":440,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":283,"left":235,"right":282,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":235,"left":232,"right":234,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":232,"left":229,"right":231,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":229,"left":226,"right":228,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":226,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":228,"left":227,"right":6,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":227,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":231,"left":7,"right":230,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":230,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":234,"left":10,"right":233,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":233,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":282,"left":246,"right":281,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":246,"left":237,"right":245,"relation":"context","nuclearity